

\begin{frame}
\frametitle{Conservation form}

The method
\[
\qinp = \qin - \DtDx (F\iph^n - F\imh^n)
\]
is in {\blue conservation form}.

\vvsp
The total mass is conserved up to fluxes at the boundaries:
\[
\Dx\sum_i \qinp = \Dx\sum_i \qin -\Dt (F_{+\infty} - F_{-\infty}).
\]

\vvsp
Note: an isolated shock must travel at the right speed!
\[
\ddt \int_{x_1}^{x_2} q(x,t)\,dx = F(x_1) - F(x_2).
\]

\end{frame}
